        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent property damage or personal injury, park the vehicle on a level surface, set the
                        parking brake, chock the wheels, and turn the engine off.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0347011" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0347011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="360px"
                         scalefitheight="472px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Heater Hose Routing</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SUPPLY HOSE FROM ENGINE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. RETURN HOSE TO TANK - SAME AS HOSE #3</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RETURN HOSE FROM STEP WELL HEATER-SAME AS HOSE #2</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SUPPLY HOSE TO STEP WELL HEATER-SAME AS HOSE #6</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. SUPPLY HOSE TO DRIVER'S SIDE HEATER-SAME AS HOSE #1</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. RETURN HOSE FROM DRIVER'S SIDE-SAME AS HOSE #4</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate and identify hoses and where cuts will be made
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0347011">(Figure 1)</hotlnk>. Pull back the loom from those areas and place a clamp
                    approximately 4 to 6 inches on both sides of the cut.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the black bracket located above Items 1 and 2 in Figure 1 and ensure gate valves
                    are closed. Place a collection tub underneath the bus to collect any leaks of engine coolant.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make the cut as noted in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0347011">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                    between hose #2 and hose #3 and install return tee fitting (Figure 2, Item 9). Use coolant on the
                    inside of the hose and on the tee fitting to make installation easier. Secure with clamps.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make the cut between hose #4 and hose #6. Make sure hose #6 will reach the return tee
                    fitting after the cut has been made
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0347012">(Figure 2)</hotlnk>. Connect hose #6 to the return tee fitting.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Push restrictor into hose #4 far enough to be able to install the supply tee fitting
                    (Figure 2). Install the tee fitting and secure with clamp.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0347012" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0347012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="376px"
                         scalefitheight="472px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Heater Hose Routing</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SUPPLY HOSE FROM ENGINE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. RETURN HOSE TO TANK</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RETURN HOSE FROM STEP WELL HEATER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SUPPLY HOSE TO STEP WELL HEATER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. RETURN HOSE FROM DRIVERS SIDE HEATER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. SUPPLY HOSE TO DRIVER'S SIDE HEATER</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. RESTRICTOR (I N SUPPLY HOSE TO STEP WELL HEATER)</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. SUPPLY TEE FITTING</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. RETURN TEE FITTING</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect hose #1 from gate valve
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0347012">(Figure 2)</hotlnk>. Cut a new piece of hose long enough to connect it
                    from the gate valve and to the supply tee fitting (Figure 2). Secure both ends with clamps and
                    install loom over hose
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0347012">(Figure 2)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Cut hose #5 to length and connect it to the supply tee fitting and secure with clamps
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0347012">(Figure 2)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Open gate valves and remove hose clamps used to stop coolant loss. Bleed air from the
                    system.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Top off coolant system and check for leaks.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect bracket and ensure hoses are clear of hood when closing.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
